==== What is CWIST? =====
CWIST is a acronym of "C Web development Is Still Trustworthy".
This aims for modern, and fast C web framework.

== What is going on? ==
- SString (with compare & substr)
- Error Codes
- HTTP Request Parsing
- HTTP Response Sending

== Notice ==
- smartstring has been renamed to sstring (see include/cwist/sstring.h and src/sstring/)

== What's next? ==
- HTTP Handlers
  - Abstract socket handlers
  - Memory-safe easy multiprocessing
- HTTP Client Support
- SString formatted printing (sprintf)
- Robust error handling in parser

== Dependency ==
- https://github.com/DaveGamble/cJSON

== What am I doing for implementing socket handler? ==
- Abstract socket listener
- Easy socket accept with handler function
  - Human-friendly error with cJSON

== Plans ==
- Memory manager
- (optional) libgc extension
- Mux Router
- CORS, HTTPS
- RestAPI Server

